<div class="uk-block uk-block-primary uk-block-muted uk-contrast">

	<div class="uk-container">

        <h3>{lang}About Tickets{/lang}</h3>
        
        <hr />
        
        <div class="uk-grid" data-uk-grid-margin>
        
            <div class="uk-width-1-1 uk-width-medium-1-2">
            
                <h4><i class="uk-icon-justify uk-icon-lightbulb-o"></i> {lang}Tickets - Bigger Tasks, Issues, Subprojects...{/lang}</h4>
                <span class="icon_list_description">{lang}Tickets are essentially tasks, but their rich features let you use them for many different things, depending on your needs. They are great for tasks that take longer time to get completed, that evolve through time, or in situations when you need to be able to discuss a task with your team or clients{/lang}.</span>
            
            </div>
            
            <div class="uk-width-1-1 uk-width-medium-1-2">
            
                <h4><i class="uk-icon-justify uk-icon-archive"></i> {lang}Organize in Categories and Associate with Milestones{/lang}</h4>
                <span class="icon_list_description">{lang}Tickets can be sorted in categories and associated with milestones; both relations are optional. Filter tickets by category using the tabs on the right. When a ticket is completed, it's moved to Archive{/lang}.</span>
            
            </div>
            
            <div class="uk-width-1-1 uk-width-medium-1-2">
            
                <h4><i class="uk-icon-justify uk-icon-check"></i> {lang}Break Into Smaller Tasks and Execute them One by One{/lang}</h4>
                <span class="icon_list_description">{lang}Use subtasks to break a ticket into smaller steps and to execute them one by one. Every subtask can have due date, priority and a list of assignees{/lang}.</span>
            
            </div>
            
            <div class="uk-width-1-1 uk-width-medium-1-2">
            
                <h4><i class="uk-icon-justify uk-icon-comment-o"></i> {lang}Have a Discussion with your Team or Clients{/lang}</h4>
                <span class="icon_list_description">{lang}Tickets can have an unlimited number of comments. Use them to discuss ticket with your colleagues and clients{/lang}.</span>
            
            </div>
            
            <div class="uk-width-1-1 uk-width-medium-1-2">
            
                <h4><i class="uk-icon-justify uk-icon-paperclip"></i> {lang}Attach Unlimited Number of Files{/lang}</h4>
                <span class="icon_list_description">{lang}People can attach any number of files to a ticket. System will use icons for various file types and thumbnails for images{/lang}.</span>
            
            </div>
            
            <div class="uk-width-1-1 uk-width-medium-1-2">
            
                <h4><i class="uk-icon-justify uk-icon-envelope"></i> {lang}Email Notifications{/lang}</h4>
                <span class="icon_list_description">{lang}Subscribe to the ticket to receive email notification when it is commented, completed or reopened. The person responsible for the ticket or assigned to it can edit the list of subscribers using Manage Subscriptions tool (available from Options menu){/lang}.</span>
            
            </div>
        
        </div>
    
    </div>

</div>